Last week the pair disrupted a meeting on the education campus and were removed by security. JOHANNESBURG - Two Wits University students have been suspended in connection with the assault of a lecturer and damaging university property.Last week the pair disrupted a meeting on the education campus and were removed by security.It's alleged that they later returned with 10 other students and attacked the lecturer and a security guard while damaging university property.One of the students, Mangaliso Sambo was arrested and appeared at the Hillbrow magistrates court on Monday, where his case was postponed to Thursday.The university's Shirona Patel said: &quot;The university will not tolerate any form of physical abuse against any members of the Wits community. And the university will act forthrightly within our rules, policies and procedures against anyone who perpetrates acts of violence on our campuses.&quot;